Jurisdictions provide a guarantee that objects stored in the bucket will remain within a specific geographic or regulatory boundary. Unlike location hints, jurisdictions are enforced constraints.

files.Summary:
Represents a location hint for R2 bucket placement.

Location hints provide a suggestion for the geographic region where the bucket's data should be stored. Cloudflare will attempt to honor this hint, but data may be placed in a nearby region if the specified location is unavailable.

Storage classes determine the cost and access characteristics of stored objects. Different classes offer trade-offs between storage cost and retrieval latency/cost.

API tokens provide fine-grained access control for Cloudflare API operations. Each token has policies that define what resources and actions are allowed.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.IApiTokensApi
files.Summary:
Defines the contract for API token management operations.

API tokens provide fine-grained access control for Cloudflare API operations. This interface handles account-scoped tokens. User-scoped tokens will be added in F17.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.ApiToken
files.Summary:
Represents an account-owned API token.

API tokens provide fine-grained access control for Cloudflare API operations. Each token has policies that define what resources and actions are allowed.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.CreateApiTokenRequest
files.Summary: Request to create a new API token.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.CreateApiTokenResult
files.Summary:
Result of creating a new API token, including the secret value.

Important: The property contains the token secret and is only available at creation time. Store it securely - it cannot be retrieved again.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.CreateTokenPolicyRequest
files.Summary: Policy definition for creating a token.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.ListApiTokensFilters
files.Summary: Filtering and pagination options for listing API tokens.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.ListPermissionGroupsFilters
files.Summary: Filtering options for listing permission groups.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.PermissionGroup
files.Summary:
Represents a permission group that can be assigned to API tokens.

Permission groups define what API operations a token can perform. Use to discover available groups.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.TokenCondition
files.Summary:
IP-based access conditions for a token.

Conditions allow restricting token usage based on the source IP address of the API request.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.TokenIpCondition
files.Summary:
IP address inclusion/exclusion rules for token access.

Supports both allowlist (in) and denylist (not_in) patterns using CIDR notation.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.TokenPermissionGroupReference
files.Summary: Reference to a permission group within a token policy.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.TokenPolicy
files.Summary:
A token policy defining allowed or denied permissions and resources.

Each policy specifies an effect (allow or deny), the permission groups that define what actions are permitted, and the resources the policy applies to.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.TokenStatus
files.Summary:
Represents the status of an API token.

Token status indicates whether the token is currently usable for API operations.

  • ActiveToken is active and can be used for API requests
  • DisabledToken has been manually disabled
  • ExpiredToken has passed its expiration date

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.UpdateApiTokenRequest
files.Summary: Request to update an existing API token.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.ApiTokens.Models.VerifyTokenResult

Provides methods for interacting with the Cloudflare Audit Logs API.

Audit logs record actions taken on account resources and are retained for 30 days.

files.Summary:
Defines the contract for audit log operations.

Audit logs provide a record of actions taken on account and user resources. Logs are retained for 30 days. This interface handles both account-scoped and user-scoped audit logs.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.AuditLogs.Models.AuditLog
files.Summary:
Represents an audit log entry recording an action taken on account resources.

Audit logs are retained for 18 months (v1 API) or 30 days (v2 API). Use filtering parameters to narrow results when querying large datasets.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.AuditLogs.Models.AuditLogAccount
files.Summary: Account context for an audit log entry.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.AuditLogs.Models.AuditLogAction

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.AuditLogs.Models.AuditLogOwner

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.AuditLogs.Models.AuditLogResource
files.Summary: Resource details for an audit log entry.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.AuditLogs.Models.AuditLogZone
files.Summary: Zone context for an audit log entry.

files.Summary:
Filtering and pagination options for listing audit logs.

All filter arrays support both inclusion and exclusion. Use the main array for inclusion, and the corresponding Not array for exclusion.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.BooleanOrStringConverter

Custom JSON converter for boolean values that can also be represented as strings.

Cloudflare's v2 audit logs API returns the action result as a string ("success"/"failure") while the v1 API returns it as a boolean. This converter handles both formats.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.CloudflareDateTimeConverter
files.Summary:
Custom JSON converter for that handles Cloudflare's non-standard date formats.

Cloudflare APIs return dates in various formats that differ from ISO 8601:

  • "2025-12-07 05:59:36.458083+00" - Space instead of 'T', short timezone offset
  • "2025-12-07T05:59:36Z" - Standard ISO 8601
  • "2025-12-07T05:59:36+00:00" - ISO 8601 with full timezone

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.CloudflareDateTimeNullableConverter
files.Summary: Custom JSON converter for nullable that handles Cloudflare's non-standard date formats.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.ExtensibleEnumConverter<T>
files.Summary:
A JSON converter for extensible enum types that implement .

This converter serializes extensible enums as their underlying string value and deserializes JSON strings back into the appropriate extensible enum type.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.ExtensibleEnumConverterFactory
files.Summary:
A JSON converter factory that automatically creates converters for any type implementing .

Register this factory with to enable automatic serialization of all extensible enum types without individual converter attributes.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.IExtensibleEnum<TSelf>
files.Summary:
Defines the contract for an extensible enum type that wraps a string value.

Extensible enums provide strong typing and IntelliSense for known values while allowing custom values to be specified when the API adds new options that the SDK doesn't yet know about.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Core.Json.JsonStringEnumMemberConverter
files.Summary: A JsonConverterFactory that creates a converter to properly handle enums decorated with EnumMemberAttribute. This allows for serialization and deserialization based on the attribute's value rather than the enum member's name.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.DnsApi

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.IDnsApi
files.Summary:
Defines the contract for DNS record operations.

All DNS operations are zone-scoped and require a zone ID. This API provides complete CRUD operations for DNS records, including single-record operations, batch operations, and import/export functionality.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.BatchDeleteOperation
files.Summary: Delete operation for batch - references a record by its ID.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.BatchDnsRecordsRequest
files.Summary:
Request to perform batch DNS record operations in a single API call.

Execution Order: Deletes Patches Puts Posts. This order ensures that deletions happen first, allowing re-creation of records with the same name in the same batch.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.BatchDnsRecordsResult
files.Summary:
Result of a batch DNS records operation.

Contains the results of each operation type. Each array contains the resulting DNS records (for creates/updates) or the deleted records (for deletes).

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.BatchPatchOperation
files.Summary:
Patch operation for batch - includes record ID and fields to update.

Only the fields you include will be updated; other fields retain their values.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.BatchPutOperation
files.Summary:
Put operation for batch - includes record ID and all fields for full replacement.

This performs a complete replacement of the record. All required fields must be provided.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.CreateDnsRecordRequest
files.Summary:
Request to create a new DNS record.

Supports all record types and optional features like comments and tags. For MX and SRV records, the Priority field is required.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.DnsImportResult
files.Summary: Represents the result of a bulk DNS record import operation.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.DnsRecord
files.Summary:
Represents a complete DNS record from the Cloudflare API.

This model includes all properties returned by the API, including optional fields like comments, tags, meta information, and record-specific settings.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.DnsRecordMeta
files.Summary:
Additional metadata for a DNS record.

Contains information about how the record was created and its source.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.DnsRecordSettings
files.Summary:
Optional settings for DNS records.

These settings control advanced DNS behavior like IPv4/IPv6-only resolution.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.DnsRecordType
files.Summary:
Represents a DNS record type supported by Cloudflare.

DNS record types define the type of data stored in a DNS record, such as IP addresses (A/AAAA), mail servers (MX), or canonical names (CNAME).

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Dns.Models.DnsScanAcceptItem

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Firewall.IZoneLockdownApi
files.Summary:
Defines the contract for managing Zone Lockdown rules.

Lockdown rules specify a list of IP addresses that are the only ones allowed to access a given URL or set of URLs.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Firewall.IZoneUaRulesApi
files.Summary:
Defines the contract for managing User-Agent blocking rules.

These rules allow you to block or challenge requests based on their User-Agent header.

files.Summary: Implements the API for managing Zone Lockdown rules.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Firewall.ZoneUaRulesApi
files.Summary: Implements the API for managing User-Agent blocking rules.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.IZonesApi
files.Summary:
Defines the contract for interacting with Cloudflare Zone resources.

This includes zone CRUD operations, DNS record management, cache purge, and all zone-level security features like IP Access Rules, WAF Rulesets, Zone Lockdown, and User-Agent blocking rules.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ActivationCheckResult
files.Summary:
Result of a zone activation check operation.

Returned by TriggerActivationCheckAsync when verifying zone activation. The API only returns the zone ID; use GetZoneDetailsAsync to fetch the updated status.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.CreateZoneRequest
files.Summary:
Request to create a new Zone in Cloudflare.

Creates a zone for a domain and associates it with an account. The domain must not already be added to Cloudflare in the same or another account.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.EditZoneRequest
files.Summary:
Request to edit a Zone's properties.

Important: Only one property can be changed per API call. Setting multiple properties in a single request may result in an error.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ListZonesFilters
files.Summary:
Filters for listing Zones.

All filter properties are optional. When multiple filters are specified, they are combined according to the parameter.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.PurgeCacheRequest
files.Summary: Defines the request payload for a cache purge operation. At least one property must be set.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.PurgeCacheResult
files.Summary: Represents the result of a successful cache purge operation.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.UpdateZoneHoldRequest
files.Summary: Request to update an existing zone hold. Both fields are optional; update only the fields you want to change.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.UpdateZoneSettingRequest<T>
files.Summary: Request to update a zone setting.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.Zone
files.Summary:
Represents the detailed information for a Cloudflare Zone.

A zone represents a domain and its configuration in Cloudflare. This record captures all properties returned by the Cloudflare API for a zone resource.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneAccount
files.Summary:
Account information nested within a Zone.

This represents the Cloudflare account that owns the zone.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneAccountReference
files.Summary:
Account reference for zone creation.

Specifies which Cloudflare account the zone should be created under.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneHold
files.Summary:
Represents the zone hold status and configuration.

A zone hold prevents creation and activation of zones with the same hostname. When include_subdomains is enabled, it also blocks all subdomains and SSL4SaaS Custom Hostnames.

Important: Zone holds are an Enterprise-only feature. The property reflects whether the hold is currently active, which depends on whether is in the past.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneMeta
files.Summary:
Metadata for a Zone.

This contains additional configuration and quota information for the zone.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneOrderField
files.Summary: Fields by which zones can be ordered in list operations.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneOwner
files.Summary:
Owner information for a Zone.

This represents the user or organization that owns the zone.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZonePlan
files.Summary:
Plan information for a Zone.

This represents the Cloudflare billing plan associated with the zone.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZonePlanReference
files.Summary:
Plan reference for zone editing.

Used to specify a plan when editing zone properties.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneSetting
files.Summary:
Represents a zone configuration setting.

The property contains the setting's current value, which varies by setting type. Use JsonElement methods to extract the appropriate type (GetString, GetInt32, etc.).

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneSettingId
files.Summary:
Represents a zone setting identifier.

Zone settings control various aspects of zone behavior including security, performance, caching, and network configuration.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneStatus
files.Summary:
Represents the status of a Cloudflare Zone.

Zone statuses indicate the current state of a zone in Cloudflare's system, such as whether it's active, pending verification, or has been moved/deleted.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneTenant
files.Summary:
Tenant information for a Zone.

This represents the tenant in a multi-tenant Cloudflare configuration.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneTenantUnit
files.Summary:
Tenant unit information for a Zone.

This represents the tenant unit in a multi-tenant Cloudflare configuration.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Models.ZoneType
files.Summary:
Represents the type of a Cloudflare Zone setup.

Zone types determine how DNS and traffic handling are configured:

  • FullDNS is fully hosted by Cloudflare
  • Partial (CNAME)DNS remains with the original provider; only specific records are proxied
  • SecondaryCloudflare acts as a secondary DNS provider

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.PolishSetting
files.Summary:
Polish (image optimization) setting for a zone.

Use with setting.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.PseudoIpv4Setting
files.Summary:
Pseudo IPv4 setting for a zone.

Use with setting.

Defines the contract for managing Rulesets at the zone level.

This includes WAF Custom Rules, Rate Limiting Rules, Redirects, and other advanced configurations for a specific zone.

files.Summary: Implements the API for managing Rulesets at the zone level.

files.Summary:
SSL/TLS encryption mode for a zone.

Use with setting.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.Tls13Setting
files.Summary:
TLS 1.3 setting value for a zone.

Use with setting.

files.Title: Cloudflare.NET.Zones.ZoneSecurityLevel
files.Summary:
Security level for a zone, controlling how aggressive Cloudflare challenges visitors.

Use with setting.

Use these constants with and methods.
